    {
      "id": "MJUe",
      "code_hash": "4befa67559dbec3e003cae56d9f15477",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"delay-state-space-to-transfer-function\">Delay state-space to transfer function</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Convert the delay state-space form of an FDN into matrix transfer function form (<code>dss_to_tf</code>). Verify by comparing the impulse response from the TF with the one from direct delay state-space simulation (<code>dss_to_impz</code>).</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>What it does:</strong></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Defines an FDN with random orthogonal feedback, random delays, and MIMO B, C, D.</li>\n<li>Converts to transfer function: <code>(tfB, tfA) = dss_to_tf(delays, A, B, C, D)</code>.</li>\n<li>Computes IR via TF: <code>mtf_to_impz(tfB, tfA, ir_len)</code>.</li>\n<li>Computes IR via delay state-space: <code>dss_to_impz(ir_len, delays, A, B, C, D)</code>.</li>\n<li>Plots poles (from <code>roots(tfA)</code>) and one channel IR (TF vs DSS), and asserts the two IRs match.</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
